# Testes de Componentes React Native

## Setup com React Native Testing Library

```tsx
import { render, screen, fireEvent, waitFor } from "@testing-library/react-native";
import { Button } from "./Button";

describe("Button", () => {
  it("renderiza com titulo correto", () => {
    render(<Button title="Salvar" onPress={jest.fn()} />);
    expect(screen.getByText("Salvar")).toBeTruthy();
  });

  it("chama onPress ao tocar", () => {
    const onPress = jest.fn();
    render(<Button title="Salvar" onPress={onPress} />);
    fireEvent.press(screen.getByText("Salvar"));
    expect(onPress).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);
  });

  it("nao chama onPress quando desabilitado", () => {
    const onPress = jest.fn();
    render(<Button title="Salvar" onPress={onPress} disabled />);
    fireEvent.press(screen.getByText("Salvar"));
    expect(onPress).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
  });
});
```

## Testando com waitFor (Assincronos)

```tsx
it("exibe dados apos carregamento", async () => {
  render(<UserProfile userId="1" />);
  expect(screen.getByTestId("loading")).toBeTruthy();
  await waitFor(() => {
    expect(screen.getByText("Joao Silva")).toBeTruthy();
  });
});
```

## Mocking de Navegacao

```tsx
const mockNavigate = jest.fn();
jest.mock("@react-navigation/native", () => ({
  useNavigation: () => ({ navigate: mockNavigate }),
  useRoute: () => ({ params: { id: "123" } }),
}));
```

## Convencoes

- Sempre usar `screen` para queries (nao destructuring do render)
- `fireEvent.press` para toques, `fireEvent.changeText` para inputs
- `waitFor` para assercoes assincronas
- `testID` como fallback quando nao ha texto acessivel
- Mock de navegacao no topo do arquivo de teste
